                            <comment id="305911" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 16:05:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The GPU RDMA changes being pushed are incompatible with the request upstream to move ko2iblnd to the generic RDMA API. Do we just update the native linux client ko2iblnd driver to this API alone and just drop the idea of moving to the Generic RDMA API for the OpenSFS tree?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="186380" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2017 23:48:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you Doug for helping out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="186373" author="doug" created="Mon, 27 Feb 2017 23:10:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A third subtask was created to adapt ko2iblnd to the RDMA memory region support code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
